  "texts": [
    "Taste-matrix complexity presents an additional challenge in gustatory research.",
    "Unlike simple chemical analyses, flavor perception arises from intricate interactions within taste matrices.",
    "Additional compounds, such as salts, fats, or acids, can modulate baseline tastes such as sweet, sour, salty, bitter, and umami.",
    "This complexity complicates AI modeling because the relationships between chemical components and sensory outputs are often nonlinear and context-dependent.",
    "Machine learning models must therefore account for these synergistic effects through multimodal input processing, combining chemical, sensory, and environmental data."
  ],
